The objective of the ALARP project is therefore to study, design and develop an innovative more efficient Automatic Track Warning System (ATWS) to improve the safety of railway trackside workers.
ALARP ATWS will able to selectively inform the trackside workers about approaching trains on the track, maintenance events on power lines and/or safety equipment in the concerned tracks that may put at risk workers’ safety (e.g. being hit by a train or by an electric shock) emergencies on tracks and tunnels nearby the workers (e.g. fires in a tunnel, toxic smoke, etc.), escape routes in case of emergencies; keep track of the status and localisation of the workers (and especially those at risk, not responding) and of the operating conditions of devices;
The proposed ALARP concept) will be based on the following main components: the track-side train presence alert device (TPAD), able to sense an approaching train on the interested track without interfering with the signalling system; a set of distributed, low-cost, wearable, context-aware, robust, trustable and highly reliable, wireless Mobile Terminals (MTs) to inform the workers about possible approaching trains and/or other events that could put at risk their safety.

The project "Come and play with us" shall offer our pupils the very best of Kindergarten learning methods. Completion of this project will result in a whole new level of knowledge of foreign languages and interdisciplinary matters in pre-primary context. . Main objectives of the project are to:
1. boost and and support development of our teachers in all domains of their professional life
2. accomplish the best possible learning conditions in the pre-primary context;
3. keep education of our pupils in accordance with the needs and challenges of today’s world; 
4. ensure to the parents that kids progression will not be impaired by participating in the program; 
5. strengthen competitiveness of the kids in globalized world; 
6. contribute to managerial skills quality of our teachers
7. support our teachers in improving their professional and linguistic skills and by that means provide for a better education quality in our Kindergarten; 
8. steer educational process to the methods that are the most natural for very young learners;
9. inspire and attract more teachers by explaining our concepts to the colleagues within the regional methodical days in Košice, Slovakia;
10. foster children’s ability of reacting to social, linguistic and cultural diversity of the world; 
The main objective of the project is to improve the methodology of teaching English to the specific audience - pupils in Kindergarten.
The particular tasks to be accomplished by the teachers have been thematically divided into methodical meetings scheduled over a period of one year as follows: 
June 2017: suggestions and solutions for particular problems - in compliance with the very young learners’ needs
July 2017: Mobility of Kindergarten teacher – 2 weeks stay at Pilgrims; Course title: METHODOLOGY AND ENGLISH LANGUAGE FOR KINDERGARTEN TEACHERS;
August 2017: Processing outcomes of the summer course into a detailed methodical plan for upcoming school year. Based on the new knowledge and experience teacher (the summer course attendee) will draft and process learning materials for teaching English in Kindergarten.
September 2017: methodical meeting of Kindergarten teachers; Training topic: Classroom management skills 
October 2017: methodical meeting of Kindergarten teachers; Training topic: Imitation and "learning by doing" - chants, songs, rhymes, storytelling and creative activities for the classroom. Opened door classroom for teachers with practical "how to do" demonstrations.
November 2017: activities focused on effective communication and communicative learning methods in Kindergarten classes December 2017: methodical meetings of Kindergarten teachers; Training topic: Listening and narrative skills. Pronunciation for teachers and learners. 
January 2018: joining/starting an eTwinning project in each classroom. Mentoring course for teachers in project management (how to start, maintain and finalize a successful project).
February 2018: methodical meeting of Kindergarten teachers; Training topic: Building a confidence in English, mainly through dramatic/theatrical activities. Building teacher’s confidence and language development. 
March 2018: online resources for teaching English to very young learners 
April 2018: information on recently published language and methodology courses and books suitable for very young learners. 
May 2018: finalising the eTwinning projects and their evaluation. Opened door classrooms with every teacher thematically focused on the project theme "Come and play with us". Preparation of a final report of key activities. Finishing the project.
We believe this project will meet set objectives, especially the one of guiding our teachers to their personal development, professional approach and improvement of their ability to: 
- communicate in English naturally, in an unforced way, and to use this skill not only in the classroom but also in any further European projects and/or exchange programs; 
- invent, design and manage projects on the regional and/or international level; 
- run the educational process in a creative way, confidently and professionally; 
- take a part in international projects on a regular basis and gain awards and/or certifications for our Kindergarten; 
- be a positive example to the colleagues from the Kindergarten sector and help them improve in their domain too; 
- become an institution well known for its unique and original approach.
